values
    ('en', 'aardvark', 'The night-digging bug vacuum animal', 'The Aardvark is a nighttime mammal with a long nose and tongue made for slurping ants and termites. It digs fast, hides underground, and comes out when the world gets cooler and quieter. For us, the message is simple: consistency can carry us through places where motivation alone cannot.'),
    ('en', 'aardwolf', 'The termite-eating ghost hyena animal', 'The Aardwolf looks like a small hyena, but instead of chasing big food it licks up termites by the thousands. It wins by choosing a different meal and a quieter path. In human life, that means flexibility keeps us effective when the world changes around us.'),
    ('en', 'abyssinian-ground-hornbill', 'The red-faced ground hornbill animal', 'The Abyssinian Ground Hornbill is a bird with bare red facial skin, huge downward-curved bill, and long-striding ground hunt. It belongs to dry savannah, thorn scrub, and open woodland where those traits help it stay effective. In human life, that means steady effort can outrun dramatic bursts that do not last.'),
