    ('en', 'addax', 'The pale dune survivor animal', 'The Addax is a desert antelope built for places that seem almost too dry for life. It survives by saving energy, moving carefully, and matching the color of the sand itself. In human life, that means flexibility keeps us effective when the world changes around us.'),
    ('en', 'adelie-penguin', 'The ice-edge commuter animal', 'The Adelie Penguin lives where ice, sea, and stone all meet. It is a little traveler of one of the hardest places on Earth, marching between colony and ocean again and again. Its lesson for us is clear: the right allies can multiply what one person can do alone.'),
    ('en', 'african-bullfrog', 'The giant puddle frog animal', 'The African Bullfrog waits out dry times underground and explodes into action when rain fills temporary pools. It turns short wet windows into a whole life plan. In human life, that means waiting for the right moment can beat forcing the wrong one.'),
    ('en', 'african-civet', 'The striped night prowler animal', 'The African Civet wanders at night with a striped coat that feels half shadow and half warning. It finds food in many ways, showing that flexibility is its real strength. For us, the message is simple: people who can adjust without losing themselves stay hard to stop.'),
    ('en', 'african-clawed-frog', 'The claw-footed pond frog animal', 'The African Clawed Frog is a amphibian with clawed hind feet, fully aquatic flat body, and murky-water suction feeding. It belongs to pond, lake, and slow river where those traits help it stay effective. For us, the message is simple: taking care of energy is often what makes long-term progress possible.'),
